# Cursor Rules for Personal Homepage Blog

## Project Structure
- Use Next.js App Router with TypeScript
- Content lives in `content/` directory (notes, articles, projects.json)
- Components are organized by purpose: `layout/`, `blog/`, `article-components/`, `ui/`
- Utilities and types are in `lib/` directory
- Custom article components can be placed in `articles/[slug]/index.tsx`

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use Zod schemas for runtime validation
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling with custom color palette
- Use shadcn/ui components as base UI primitives

## Content Management
- Notes: Short, frequent posts in `content/notes/*.mdx`
- Articles: Longer pieces in `content/articles/*.mdx` with optional custom components
- Projects: JSON file at `content/projects.json`
- All MDX files must have frontmatter validated by Zod schemas
- Frontmatter fields: title (string), date (string), tags (string[]), featuredImage (optional string)

## Component Patterns
- Blog components (NoteCard, ArticleCard, etc.) should accept data props and be reusable
- Article components (Blockquote, CodeBlock, Separator) support customization via props
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional className merging
- Prefer composition over configuration

## Styling Guidelines
- Use custom color palette defined in `app/globals.css`
- Playfair Display for headings (serif), Manrope for body (sans-serif)
- Match Trent Walton aesthetic: clean, minimal, readable
- Use semantic HTML and proper accessibility attributes

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `NoteCard.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `reading-time.ts`)
- Pages: Next.js conventions (e.g., `page.tsx`, `[slug]/page.tsx`)
- Content: kebab-case for MDX files (e.g., `my-note.mdx`)

## Best Practices
- Always validate frontmatter with Zod schemas
- Use `generateStaticParams` for static pages
- Prefer static generation over server-side rendering
- Handle missing content gracefully (notFound())
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Calculate reading time for all content

## AI Assistance Guidelines
- When adding new content, ensure frontmatter matches schema
- When creating custom article components, check if they should be in `articles/[slug]/` or imported in MDX
- Maintain consistent styling and component patterns
- Keep components focused and reusable
